data.description: Provides a theoretical and research framework for understanding suicide, to develop understanding of the experiences of those who are suicidal, and to introduce prevention, assessment, and treatment approaches. Topics will include common myths related to suicide, and research challenging those myths; suicide assessment, intervention, and prevention strategies; suicide bereavement; ethical and legal issues related to suicide; and the experiences of populations disproportionately affected by suicide.
data.title: PSYCHOLOGY OF SUICIDE
